<title>PORTUGAL: ESCUDO TRADES CALM VS MARK, SEEN HOLDING STEADY.</title>
<headline>ESCUDO TRADES CALM VS MARK, SEEN HOLDING STEADY.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1997-08-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>The escudo quietly traded steadily against the mark, and traders expected it to continue in moderate trade throughout Tuesday's session.</p>
<p>The escudo was trading at 101.15/18 to the mark against its 101.16/21 close on Monday.</p>
<p>Traders said the Bundesbank's decision to leave its repo rate unchanged at three percent had calmed immediate fears of a German rate rise to help the mark.</p>
<p>--Lisbon bureau 3511-3150035</p>
